				<td colspan="2"><div class="postbody">From the onset, I would think that is a great idea.  However thinking about it a bit more, I am not sure if I would agree with the plan.
<br />

<br />
First off, at least in the US, people may claim that as cruel and unusual punishment.  However, you can get sued for monetary rewards in a civil case (e.g. O.J. Simpson).
<br />

<br />
But, what about the family of the incarcerated?  They may well be fully innocent (you are until proven guilty) and to deprive them of money to pay for the cost of jailling a family member will in turn harm that family unnecessarily.<span class="gensmall"></span>


				</div></td>
