			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><div class="postbody">Having prisoners help pay in some way for their incarceration: yes.
<br />

<br />
Taxpayers shouldn't have to foot the entire bill.
<br />

<br />
But of course this gets tough when saw the husband is being locked up because of violence he did on the family. Then you have a family suffering monetarily after suffering physically.  And in these cases, the family oftentimes needs any funds they have since the husband is gone and no longer providing income.
<br />

<br />
Sometimes prisoners are put to work while serving time to help offset the costs.  I think this needs to be more common.<span class="gensmall"></span>


				</div></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
